[0.0, "o", "\u001b[2J\u001b[H"]
[0.3, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;44m  a11y-checker\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[0.9, "o", "\u001b[38;5;245m  what 26 real accessibility audits taught us — and where it showed up next\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.5, "o", "\u001b[2J\u001b[H"]
[3.8, "o", "\u001b[38;5;176m\u001b[1m  ┄┄ the bug that kept coming back ┄┄\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.8, "o", "\r\n"]
[4.6, "o", "\u001b[38;5;245m  Across 26 real audits, one failure showed up more than any other:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[7.615, "o", "\u001b[38;5;245m  a search box a screen reader cannot name.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[9.95, "o", "\u001b[38;5;245m  You see a box that says “Search documentation…”\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[12.155, "o", "\u001b[38;5;245m  A blind user tabs to it and hears: “edit, blank.”  No idea what it's for.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[16.03, "o", "\u001b[38;5;245m  \u001b[38;5;221m22 of those 26 organizations shipped this exact bug.\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[20.135, "o", "\u001b[2J\u001b[H"]
[20.435, "o", "\u001b[38;5;176m\u001b[1m  ┄┄ then we pointed it at shadcn/ui ┄┄\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[20.435, "o", "\r\n"]
[21.235, "o", "\u001b[38;5;245m  taxonomy — shadcn's own example app. ~25k stars.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[23.485, "o", "\u001b[38;5;245m  The code thousands of React devs copy from. Here's its search box:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
