[60.416, "o", "  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;252msearch.tsx\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[60.476, "o", "  \u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;252m  search.tsx:27\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[60.536, "o", "  \u001b[38;5;245m    rule:   \u001b[38;5;176menforce/input-no-name\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;245m  \u001b[38;5;203m\u001b[1m[block]\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;245m  \u001b[38;5;44m\u001b[1m(call-site content check)\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[60.596, "o", "  \u001b[38;5;245m    wcag:   \u001b[38;5;252mWCAG 1.3.1\u001b[38;5;245m, \u001b[38;5;252mWCAG 3.3.2\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[60.656, "o", "  \u001b[38;5;245m    Control resolves to a form input but has no associated label: no aria-label/aria-labelledby, no label/title prop, and no id to pair with a <label for>. Associate a real label (corpus: 1.3.1 / 3.3.2-form-control-no-name).\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[60.716, "o", "  \u001b[38;5;245m    severity: \u001b[38;5;203m\u001b[1mCRITICAL\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[60.776, "o", "  \u001b[38;5;245m    corpus: \u001b[38;5;221m[VERY COMMON]\u001b[38;5;245m SC 1.3.1 — \u001b[38;5;221m\u001b[1m22/26 orgs\u001b[0m\u001b[38;5;245m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[60.836, "o", "  \u001b[38;5;36m    fix:    Use real semantics: associate every form field with a <label> via id (not placeholder-only); use <ul>/<li> or <table> for lists; wrap main content in <main> and footer in <footer>.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[60.896, "o", "\u001b[0m"]
[60.896, "o", "\r\n"]
[63.096, "o", "\u001b[38;5;245m  \u001b[38;5;44m(call-site content check)\u001b[38;5;245m — that's the line eslint can't produce.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[68.656, "o", "\u001b[2J\u001b[H"]
[68.956, "o", "\r\n"]
[68.956, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;252m  One line of config taught it your design system.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[70.556, "o", "\u001b[1m\u001b[38;5;252m  Now the bug 22 orgs missed never reaches your users.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[72.556, "o", "\r\n"]
[72.556, "o", "  \u001b[38;5;245meslint:\u001b[0m clean    \u001b[38;5;245m·\u001b[0m    \u001b[38;5;44m\u001b[1ma11y-checker:\u001b[0m caught it, ranked it, handed you the fix.\r\n"]
